WEBVTT

00:01.389 --> 00:02.271
We're the new guys.

00:02.271 --> 00:04.669
He is officially the grossest
person I've ever met.

00:04.669 --> 00:06.654
–A post-nup?
–My idea.

00:06.654 --> 00:08.990
–She gets my Cigarette boat?
–Only if you cheat.

00:08.990 --> 00:11.476
We met on Facespace.
Today is our first real date.

00:11.476 --> 00:13.710
Denny, it's me,
Bethany.

00:13.710 --> 00:16.827
When you called me a “midget”,
you caused me emotional distress.

00:16.827 --> 00:19.182
Judge Marcia Hooper was
found murdered last night.

00:19.182 --> 00:20.199
We were having an affair.

00:20.199 --> 00:22.101
Could my son actually be arrested?

00:22.101 --> 00:24.795
<i>They wouldn't be hauling him away in
cuffs, if they didn't have the goods on him.</i>

00:24.795 --> 00:27.861
<i>–Maybe I should do it.
–You mean, kill judge Hooper?</i>

00:27.861 --> 00:30.435
<i>Maybe *he* wants me to kill her.</i>

00:36.365 --> 00:38.149
<i>He just happened to be
at the murder scene.</i>

00:38.149 --> 00:40.728
<i>He just happened to be having
a sweet little affair with the victim.</i>

00:40.728 --> 00:41.529
<i>Oh!</i>

00:41.529 --> 00:45.951
<i>And he just happened to be having a
teenie-weenie little dream about killing her.</i>

00:45.951 --> 00:49.535
<i>I might have been born yesterday, folks,
but I wasn't born last night!</i>

00:49.535 --> 00:52.025
<i>Does anybody really think
he didn't kill her?</i>

00:52.025 --> 00:55.117
My God! We need to gag this woman.

00:55.117 --> 00:56.359
I did once.

00:56.359 --> 00:58.611
Best sexual experience of my life.

00:58.611 --> 00:59.844
What are you talking about?

00:59.844 --> 01:02.439
She covered one of my trials.

01:02.439 --> 01:05.053
She's an animal.

01:05.459 --> 01:07.568
You had sex with this reporter?

01:07.568 --> 01:09.049
Please, Paul.

01:09.049 --> 01:10.966
A gentleman never talks.

01:10.966 --> 01:14.555
<i>Get with the program, folks,
this guy is guilty as sin.</i>

01:14.555 --> 01:15.883
She's an animal.

01:15.883 --> 01:18.282
Danny, she seems to be on the attack.

01:18.282 --> 01:20.556
Did it end badly?

01:20.807 --> 01:22.595
Not for me.

01:29.935 --> 01:32.855
Your honour,
Jeffrey Coho.

01:32.855 --> 01:35.349
I wanted to introduce myself,
convey my deepest—

01:35.349 --> 01:37.161
I know who you are, Mr Coho.

01:37.161 --> 01:40.690
You're the man giving representation
to the person who murdered my wife.

01:40.690 --> 01:43.806
Your Honour, I don't believe
Scott Little took the life of your wife.

01:43.806 --> 01:46.020
I wouldn't defend him
if I thought that he did.

01:46.020 --> 01:49.154
Because you don't defend
guilty people, is that it?

01:49.154 --> 01:51.317
–You disgust me.
–Already?

01:51.317 --> 01:54.630
It's not enough that you tried to secure the
freedom of an adulterer and a murderer—

01:54.630 --> 01:57.249
We both want the real killer
brought to justice here.

01:57.249 --> 01:59.438
It's not Scott Little.

02:00.402 --> 02:02.312
Get out!

02:03.292 --> 02:05.495
If I may ask,

02:05.495 --> 02:09.882
there are rumours that your wife's infidelity
extended significantly beyond my client.

02:09.882 --> 02:11.928
Did you know about this?

02:11.928 --> 02:16.629
How dare you come into this room, and
indict not only my late wife—

02:16.629 --> 02:18.525
–Don't want to be insensitive—
–but also my marriage?

02:18.525 --> 02:20.993
…to the person who killed your wife—

02:20.993 --> 02:22.579
Your client murdered my wife.

02:22.579 --> 02:24.074
–…because I'm told—
–Get out of my chambers!

02:24.074 --> 02:28.316
…that you've told other people
that your marriage was in trouble.

02:28.316 --> 02:32.084
–Who told you that?
–They insisted on anonymity.

02:32.084 --> 02:33.633
Your Honour, please.

02:33.633 --> 02:36.572
We all want to get to
the truth of this.

02:36.931 --> 02:38.808
Jonathan, what are you doing here?

02:38.808 --> 02:40.562
I hope nothing <i>ex parte</i>.

02:40.562 --> 02:43.629
One of my staff saw you come here.
What are you doing?

02:43.629 --> 02:45.780
Trying to find out
who killed Marcia Hooper.

02:45.780 --> 02:47.708
Don't you wanna know?
–Are you kidding me?

02:47.708 --> 02:49.867
Certainly I'm allowed to interview
potential witnesses,

02:49.867 --> 02:52.334
don't tell me the tampering
is already begun.

02:52.334 --> 02:53.612
You are out of your mind.

02:53.612 --> 02:56.845
Yes, how nice to remain
so tightly locked inside yours.

02:56.845 --> 02:58.521
Let me tell you something
right now.

02:58.521 --> 03:00.166
If you start to intimidate
my witnesses—

03:00.166 --> 03:03.480
–Why yours? Do you have dibs?

03:03.824 --> 03:06.579
Is this the way
you wanna play it?

03:06.579 --> 03:08.172
Fine.

03:08.172 --> 03:11.462
Doesn't seem we can
settle this with words.

03:12.361 --> 03:14.669
Maybe we should fight.

03:19.171 --> 03:22.219
Why does everyone in Boston
just stare at me?

